            <h2>Food Safety Guidelines for Donations</h2>

            <h4>1. General Food Safety Rules</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="icon">✅</span> <b>Only Donate Fresh & Safe Food:</b> Free from spoilage, mold, or unusual odors.</li>
                <li><span class="icon">✅</span> <b>Check Expiry Dates:</b> Ensure packaged food has a valid expiration date.</li>
                <li><span class="icon">✅</span> <b>Properly Stored Food:</b> Keep perishable food at appropriate temperatures.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>2. Safe Handling Practices</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>🔹 <b>Wash Hands:</b> Always wash hands before handling food.</li>
                <li>🔹 <b>Use Clean Utensils & Containers:</b> Avoid contamination risks.</li>
                <li>🔹 <b>Avoid Cross-Contamination:</b> Keep raw and cooked foods separate.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>3. Acceptable & Non-Acceptable Food Items</h4>
            <h5>✔️ What You Can Donate</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>Fresh fruits and vegetables (washed properly)</li>
                <li>Cooked meals (properly packed)</li>
                <li>Sealed, unopened, and non-expired packaged food</li>
                <li>Baked goods (without dairy-based fillings)</li>
                <li>Dry foods like rice, pasta, and grains</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>❌ What You Should Not Donate</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>Leftovers from personal meals</li>
                <li>Expired, moldy, or spoiled food</li>
                <li>Opened or partially consumed packaged food</li>
                <li>Raw meat or seafood (unless properly stored and handled)</li>
                <li>Alcoholic beverages</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>4. Storage & Transport Guidelines</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>🚛 <b>Proper Temperature Control:</b> Keep hot food above <b>60°C (140°F)</b> and cold food below <b>5°C (41°F)</b>.</li>
                <li>📦 <b>Use Airtight Containers:</b> Prevent contamination.</li>
                <li>🚿 <b>Label and Date:</b> Clearly mark the preparation date and food type.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>5. Hygiene & Health Considerations</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>If you’re feeling sick, avoid handling food donations.</li>
                <li>Use gloves or clean utensils when packaging food.</li>
                <li>Ensure food is cooked thoroughly to avoid bacteria growth.</li>
            </ul>
